    "description": "Discover a unique and fully interactive lava simulator !<br>Watch eruptions and lava flows across the stunning landscapes of Réunion Island.<br>This simulation was co-created in 2016 with Eric Chahi, the renowned author of Another World, From Dust, and Paper Beast !<br><br>The simulator lets you interact in real time with eruptions in photorealistic, dynamic environments, revealing a wide range of volcanic structures, from lava fields to cones creation !<br>Create new eruptive fissures, control flow rate, temperature, pressure, and observe the evolution in beautifully rendered 3D landscapes !<br><br>The application is powered by a custom-built graphics and physics engine, specifically designed for this simulation and using the incredible computing power of GPUs !<br><br><strong>Useful Keyboard Shortcuts</strong><br>• <strong>Mouse, middle button</strong> : move the camera from the observer’s point of view<br>• <strong>Alt + middle button</strong> : rotate the camera<br>• <strong>C or double-click</strong> : center the camera on the selected point<br>• <strong>W</strong> : Wireframe view<br>• <strong>N</strong> : Normal map view<br>• <strong>Break</strong> : start / pause the simulation<br>• <strong>+</strong> / <strong>-</strong> : increase / decrease simulation speed<br>• <strong>Escape</strong> : open the main menu, with access to scenarios and graphic settings<br>• <strong>F12</strong> : Steam screen capture",
